64.about:
I have made significant contributions in the area of digital signal processing and recognition. 
I would like to further apply my research skills in the development of methodological tools in signal processing at various stages of the acquisition, processing and analysis and their applications, especially on biomedical signals such as EEG and ECG signals.
Also, an interesting area which I am eager to delve into is biomedical image processing, analysis, and classification. Finding the interesting characteristics from MRI imaging would be a major contribution step towards successful diagnostic.

Research Interests:

Audio/Image signal processing;
Computer audition including noise-robust sound recognition;
Speech/Speaker recognition;
Analysis of ECG/EEG signals;
Audio source separation in various environmental conditions;
Sound information retrieval;
Machine learning and modeling;

